---
title: One-Pan Cheesy Beef Tacos with Black Beans, Green Pepper & Smoky Red Pepper
description: We love making tacos at home so we can customize them to fit our exact craving. For this vegetarian version, we ditched the meat for a hearty filling of green pepper and spiced black beans, and two cheeses for maximum melt-factor, plus a drizzle of smoky red pepper crema. Oh, and did we mention these are ready in just 15 minutes?
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/661d64d63d20ae432f30b528-0e7d7a3b.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/66aa60ed915008628f446447-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-cheesy-beef-tacos-66aa60ed915008628f446447
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Mexican
nutrition:
  calories: 1210 kcal
  fat: 68 g
  saturated fat: 27 g
  carbohydrates: 85 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 55 g
  fiber: 11 g
  sodium: 2290 mg
servings: 2
time required: 15 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, deseed, and thinly slice @Long Green Pepper{1}(halved and deseeded)
crosswise into strips. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced),
separating whites from greens.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add @Ground Beef{10%ounce}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes}.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160º.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add green pepper
and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> If needed, add a splash of water to help green pepper soften.

Add green pepper to pan with beef (skip the oil); cook through this step as
instructed.

While green pepper cooks, drain @Black Beans{1}(drained) and rinse.

Once green pepper is softened, stir in scallion whites and
@Southwest Spice Blend{2%teaspoons}. Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

> 4 tsp for 4 servings; be sure to measure—we sent more.

Add beans, @Tex-Mex Paste{1%unit}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Cook, stirring, until
filling has combined and thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Sprinkle bean filling with @Cheddar Cheese{1/2%cup} and
@Mexican Cheese Blend{1/2%cup}. Cover pan until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Wrap @Flour Tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and
pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with bean filling,
@Smoky Red Pepper Crema{2%tablespoons}, and scallion greens. Serve.